2015 my parents came over as I couldn’t fly down, 2016 and 2019 were fine. That’s half my flights home for Christmas since I’ve been living in the UK. 🤦🏻‍♀️

2017: A suspected hijacked plane made an emergency landing in Malta the day before my flight. All flights were being diverted to Sicily . Since I was the first flight out the following morning, my dad bought a Catamaran ticket to Sicily to meet me there. Thankfully it was fine.

2018: Dronegate at Gatwick. I was one of 100,000 people stranded at Gatwick Airport because someone decided to fly their drone. I had to get a train back to my flat and fly out 3 days later. I managed to find a seat just in time for Christmas day.

2020: All commercial flights to Malta cancelled, with mine moving from a Saturday to a Friday. Made it home but then I had to buy a £200 one way ticket back because my Ryanair flight got cancelled (all flights were, reparation only, which is what I had to buy)
